{
  "text": "In our case, in spite of performing a breast reduction pattern, large flaps were still needed. Some articles described the increased donor site morbidity in abdominal free flaps with regards to the amount of fascia harvested 7 or when bipedicled flaps were dissected. [CITATION_1] In our case, although unintentionally, three flaps were obtained and just one abdominal fascia incision. These findings could be of interest when needing large volumes, reducing the number of flaps needed thus saving operating time and reducing the risk of donor site complications.",
  "citation_candidates": [
